{{Quote|I merely wish a servant. Someone who will be waiting there for me when I return. Formed from one of the Emperor's prize souvenirs&mdash;sample B-2332-54, I believe it was.|Jedi Master Joruus C'baoth|<ref name="The Last Command">''[[The Last Command]]''</ref>}}
'''Sample B-2332-54''' was the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] sorting code for [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] [[Cho mai/Legends|severed]] right [[Limb/Legends|hand]], which he lost in a [[Duel on Cloud City/Legends|lightsaber duel]] with [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] in [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin's]] [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]] in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].

The [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaught]] [[Engineer/Legends|engineer]] [[Groggin]] first discovered the hand in the bowels of Cloud City, along with [[Anakin Skywalker's second lightsaber/Legends|Skywalker's lightsaber]]. Vader recovered the hand and the [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] from Groggin and immediately delivered them to [[Mount Tantiss/Legends|Mount Tantiss]], [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] private storehouse on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Wayland/Legends|Wayland]]. The hand became one of the [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor's]] prized trophies.

In [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], the [[Clone madness|mad]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Joruus C'baoth]] utilized sample B-2332-54 to create a Skywalker [[Cloning/Legends|clone]], named [[Luuke Skywalker]], in a failed attempt at [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] dominion.

